<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="338" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[103,753,603,660]" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis box="[148,414,603,627]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[446,632,603,627]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="15" pageNumber="338" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilaris">
<emphasis box="[446,632,603,627]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">Benstonea pilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the rainforests of Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[436,534,636,660]" name="Malaysia" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="STONE" box="[549,687,636,660]" firstAuthor="STONE" pageId="15" pageNumber="338" pagination="609 - 613" refId="ref16142" refString="STONE, B. C. (1969). Studies in the Malesian Pandanaceae, VI. The identity of &quot; Pandanus pilaris &quot; Ridley. Webbia 23: 609 - 613." type="journal article" year="1969">STONE, 1969</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="338" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[103,754,676,927]" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">
<emphasis box="[148,290,676,700]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">Observations</emphasis>
. – The type collection 
<emphasis box="[539,669,676,700]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">(Ridley s.n.)</emphasis>
has not been found in SING, but a steril duplicate has recently been rediscovered by HB at Kew, which is here designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[103,209,773,797]" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">lectotype</typeStatus>
. In 
<bibRefCitation author="STONE, B. C." box="[252,395,773,797]" journalOrPublisher="Fed. Mus. J." pageId="15" pageNumber="338" pagination="1 - 74" part="23" refId="ref16436" refString="STONE, B. C. (1978). Revisio Pandanacearum, Part I. Pandanus subgenera Coronata and Acrostigma. Flora Malesiana precursores. Fed. Mus. J. 23: 1 - 74." title="Revisio Pandanacearum, Part I. Pandanus subgenera Coronata and Acrostigma. Flora Malesiana precursores" type="journal article" year="1978">1978, STONE</bibRefCitation>
designated a specimen at KLU 
<emphasis box="[103,356,806,830]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">(Mahmud &amp; Sharif s.n.)</emphasis>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[428,514,806,830]" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">neotype</typeStatus>
, but the rediscovery of the type revokes this nomenclatural act. As 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">Mahmud &amp; Sharif s.n.</emphasis>
is a fertile collection including a complete syncarp, and clearly belongs to 
<taxonomicName box="[306,401,903,927]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="15" pageNumber="338" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pilaris">
<emphasis box="[306,401,903,927]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="338">B.pilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we designate it as the epitype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
